  "solution": [
    "## Solutions to Limits - Basic Concepts Exercises",
    "",
    "### Exercise 1: Intuitive Understanding of Limits",
    "",
    "**a)** As x approaches 2 (but x ≠ 2), f(x) gets arbitrarily close to 3",
    "",
    "**b)** f(x) → 9 as x → 3",
    "",
    "**c)** f(x) → 1 as x → 0",
    "",
    "**d)** f(x) → 3 as x → 1 (derivative of x³ at x=1)",
    "",
    "**e)** Standard limit, used in derivative of sin x",
    "",
    "### Exercise 2: One-Sided Limits",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→2⁺} (x² - 4)/(x - 2) = lim_{x→2⁺} (x+2) = 4",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→2⁻} (x² - 4)/(x - 2) = lim_{x→2⁻} (x+2) = 4",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→0⁺} 1/x = +∞",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→0⁻} 1/x = -∞",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→1⁺} (x-1)/(x²-1) = lim_{x→1⁺} (x-1)/((x-1)(x+1)) = lim_{x→1⁺} 1/(x+1) = 1/2",
    "",
    "### Exercise 3: Limits at Finite Points",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→3} (x² - 9)/(x - 3) = lim_{x→3} (x+3) = 6",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→-2} (x³ + 8)/(x + 2) = lim_{x→-2} (x² - 2x + 4) = 4 + 4 + 4 = 12",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→1} (x^n - 1)/(x - 1) = n (by derivative of x^n)",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→a} (x² - a²)/(x - a) = lim_{x→a} (x+a) = 2a",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→0} (sin x)/x = 1",
    "",
    "### Exercise 4: Limits at Infinity",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→∞} 1/x = 0",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→∞} x/(x+1) = 1",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→∞} (2x² + 3x - 1)/(x² + 2x + 1) = 2",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→-∞} e^x = 0",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→∞} ln x = ∞",
    "",
    "### Exercise 5: Limit Laws - Sum and Difference",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→2} x² = 4, lim_{x→2} 3x = 6, lim_{x→2} 1 = 1, so 4 + 6 - 1 = 9",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→1} x³ = 1, lim_{x→1} x² = 1, lim_{x→1} x = 1, lim_{x→1} 1 = 1, so 1 - 1 + 1 - 1 = 0",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→0} sin x = 0, lim_{x→0} cos x = 1, so 0 + 1 = 1",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→2} x² = 4, lim_{x→2} 4x = 8, lim_{x→2} 4 = 4, so 4 - 8 + 4 = 0",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→-1} x³ = -1, lim_{x→-1} x² = 1, lim_{x→-1} x = -1, lim_{x→-1} 1 = 1, so -1 + 1 - 1 + 1 = 0",
    "",
    "### Exercise 6: Limit Laws - Product and Quotient",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→3} (x-1) = 2, lim_{x→3} (x-2) = 1, so 2 × 1 = 2",
    "",
    "**b)** Does not exist (oscillates between -1 and 1)",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→1} (x²-1) = 0, lim_{x→1} (x-1) = 0, but lim_{x→1} (x+1) = 2, so 0/0 = 2",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→2} (x²-4) = 0, lim_{x→2} (x²-3x+2) = 0, lim_{x→2} (x-2) = 0, so 0/0 = 1",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→0} tan x = 0, lim_{x→0} sin x = 0, so 0/0 = 1",
    "",
    "### Exercise 7: Limit Laws - Constant Multiple",
    "",
    "**a)** 5 × lim_{x→4} (x-2) = 5 × 2 = 10",
    "",
    "**b)** -2 × lim_{x→0} sin x = -2 × 0 = 0",
    "",
    "**c)** 3 × lim_{x→1} (x² + 2x - 1) = 3 × (1 + 2 - 1) = 3 × 2 = 6",
    "",
    "**d)** -3 × lim_{x→-2} (x+2)² = -3 × 0 = 0",
    "",
    "**e)** (1/2) × lim_{x→3} (x+3) = (1/2) × 6 = 3",
    "",
    "### Exercise 8: Squeeze Theorem",
    "",
    "**a)** -x² ≤ x² cos(1/x) ≤ x², lim -x² = 0, lim x² = 0, so lim = 0",
    "",
    "**b)** -|x| ≤ x sin(1/x) ≤ |x|, lim = 0",
    "",
    "**c)** -|x³| ≤ x³ ≤ |x³|, but sin x oscillates, limit doesn't exist",
    "",
    "**d)** -x² ≤ x² sin(1/x²) ≤ x², lim = 0",
    "",
    "**e)** -1/x ≤ (sin x)/x ≤ 1/x, lim = 0",
    "",
    "### Exercise 9: Limits of Trigonometric Functions",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→0} sin x = 0",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→0} cos x = 1",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→0} tan x = 0",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→π/2} tan x = ∞",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→0} sin(2x)/x = lim_{x→0} 2 sin(2x)/(2x) = 2 × 1 = 2",
    "",
    "### Exercise 10: Limits of Exponential Functions",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→0} e^x = 1",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→∞} e^x = ∞",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→-∞} e^x = 0",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→0} (e^x - 1)/x = 1",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→∞} (1 + 1/x)^x = e",
    "",
    "### Exercise 11: Limits of Logarithmic Functions",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→1} ln x = 0",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→∞} ln x = ∞",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→0⁺} ln x = -∞",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→0⁺} x ln x = 0",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→∞} (ln x)/x = 0",
    "",
    "### Exercise 12: Piecewise Functions and Limits",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→2} x² = 4, but f(2) = 5, so limit exists but function not continuous",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→1⁻} (x+1) = 2, lim_{x→1⁺} x² = 1, limits different, no limit",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→0⁻} sin x = 0, lim_{x→0⁺} x = 0, so lim = 0 = f(0)",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→0⁻} 1/x = -∞, lim_{x→0⁺} x² = 0, limits different, no limit",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→0⁻} e^x = 1, lim_{x→0⁺} ln x = -∞, no limit",
    "",
    "### Exercise 13: Limits and Asymptotes",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→∞} x/(x+1) = 1, horizontal asymptote y=1",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→2⁺} 1/(x-2) = ∞, lim_{x→2⁻} 1/(x-2) = -∞, vertical asymptote x=2",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→∞} x²/(x²-1) = 1, horizontal y=1; vertical at x=±1",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→∞} e^x / x = ∞, no horizontal; vertical none",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→-1⁺} ln(x+1) = -∞, vertical asymptote x=-1",
    "",
    "### Exercise 14: Limits in Applications",
    "",
    "**a)** Definition of derivative, instantaneous rate of change",
    "",
    "**b)** Function is continuous at a if limit equals function value",
    "",
    "**c)** Riemann sum, foundation of definite integrals",
    "",
    "**d)** Carrying capacity or unbounded growth",
    "",
    "**e)** Resistance in circuits, approaches 0 as resistance increases",
    "",
    "### Exercise 15: Challenging Limits",
    "",
    "**a)** lim_{x→0} (1 - cos x)/x² = 1/2",
    "",
    "**b)** lim_{x→0} (e^x - 1 - x)/x² = 1/2",
    "",
    "**c)** lim_{x→0} (sin x - x)/x³ = -1/6",
    "",
    "**d)** lim_{x→∞} (x² + 3x)/(x³ - 2x² + 1) = 0",
    "",
    "**e)** lim_{x→0⁺} x^x = 1"
